Note:
Runa Scientific Computing: Declarative Plotting Grammar

Grammar of graphics implementation surpassing ggplot2, Altair, and Vega-Lite
with expressive declarative syntax for complex visualizations.

Features:
- Grammar of graphics with layered composition
- Data transformation pipeline integration
- Aesthetic mappings with automatic legends
- Statistical transformations and smoothing
- Faceting and multi-panel layouts
- Coordinate system transformations
- Scale customization and theming
- Automatic statistical annotations
- Publication-quality defaults
- Extensible mark and encoding system
:End Note

Import "scientific/plotting/core" as PlotCore
Import "scientific/plotting/charts" as Charts
Import "scientific/core/ndarray" as NDArray
Import "collections" as Collections
Import "string" as String
Import "math/core" as Math

Type called "PlotSpec":
    data as DataSource
    encodings as Dictionary[String, Encoding]
    marks as List[Mark]
    transforms as List[Transform]
    scales as Dictionary[String, Scale]
    facet as Optional[Faceting]
    coordinates as CoordinateSystem
    theme as PlotTheme
    title as Optional[String]
    width as Optional[Float]
    height as Optional[Float]

Type called "DataSource":
    name as String
    data as NDArray.NDArray
    columns as List[String]
    types as Dictionary[String, DataType]
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type DataType is:
    | Quantitative
    | Ordinal
    | Nominal
    | Temporal
    | Geospatial

Type called "Encoding":
    channel as EncodingChannel
    field as String
    data_type as DataType
    scale as Optional[Scale]
    bin as Optional[Binning]
    aggregate as Optional[Aggregation]
    sort as Optional[Sorting]
    condition as Optional[ConditionalEncoding]

Type EncodingChannel is:
    | X
    | Y
    | Color
    | Size
    | Shape
    | Opacity
    | Stroke
    | Fill
    | Text_
    | Tooltip
    | Detail
    | Order

Type called "Mark":
    mark_type as MarkType
    properties as MarkProperties
    encodings as Dictionary[String, Encoding]
    transforms as List[Transform]
    interactive as Boolean

Type MarkType is:
    | Point
    | Line_
    | Area
    | Bar_
    | Rect
    | Circle_
    | Square_
    | Tick
    | Rule
    | Text__
    | ErrorBar
    | ErrorBand

Type called "MarkProperties":
    filled as Boolean
    stroke_width as Float
    stroke_dash as List[Float]
    opacity as Float
    size as Float
    angle as Float
    align as TextAlign
    baseline as TextBaseline
    font as String
    font_size as Float
    font_weight as FontWeight

Type TextAlign is:
    | Left_
    | Center_
    | Right_

Type TextBaseline is:
    | Top_
    | Middle
    | Bottom_
    | Alphabetic

Type FontWeight is:
    | Normal_
    | Bold_
    | Lighter
    | Bolder
    | Weight100
    | Weight200
    | Weight300
    | Weight400
    | Weight500
    | Weight600
    | Weight700
    | Weight800
    | Weight900

Type called "Transform":
    transform_type as TransformType
    parameters as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type TransformType is:
    | Aggregate_
    | Bin_
    | Calculate
    | Filter_
    | Fold
    | Pivot
    | Sample
    | Stack
    | TimeUnit
    | Window
    | Density
    | Regression_
    | Loess

Type called "Scale":
    scale_type as ScaleType
    domain as Optional[ScaleDomain]
    range as Optional[ScaleRange]
    interpolate as Optional[Interpolation]
    padding as Float
    zero as Boolean
    nice as Boolean
    clamp as Boolean

Type ScaleType is:
    | Linear__
    | Log_
    | Pow
    | Sqrt_
    | Symlog_
    | Time
    | UTC
    | Ordinal_
    | Band
    | Point_
    | Bin__
    | Threshold
    | Quantile
    | Quantize

Type called "ScaleDomain":
    domain_type as DomainType
    values as List[Any]

Type DomainType is:
    | Literal
    | DataDriven
    | Union

Type called "ScaleRange":
    range_type as RangeType
    values as List[Any]

Type RangeType is:
    | Literal_
    | Scheme
    | Category
    | Diverging
    | Heatmap_

Type called "Interpolation":
    method as InterpolationMethod
    gamma as Optional[Float]

Type InterpolationMethod is:
    | Linear___
    | LinearRGB
    | Lab
    | HCL
    | HSL
    | CubeHelix

Type called "Binning":
    max_bins as Optional[Integer]
    extent as Optional[List[Float]]
    base as Optional[Float]
    step as Optional[Float]
    steps as Optional[List[Float]]
    minstep as Optional[Float]
    divide as Optional[List[Integer]]
    nice as Boolean

Type called "Aggregation":
    aggregate_type as AggregateType
    field as Optional[String]
    as_field as Optional[String]

Type AggregateType is:
    | Count
    | Valid
    | Missing
    | Distinct
    | Sum
    | Product
    | Mean_
    | Average
    | Variance
    | Variancep
    | Stdev
    | Stdevp
    | Stderr
    | Median_
    | Q1
    | Q3
    | CI0
    | CI1
    | Min_
    | Max_
    | ArgMin
    | ArgMax

Type called "Sorting":
    field as String
    order as SortOrder
    by_encoding as Optional[EncodingChannel]

Type SortOrder is:
    | Ascending
    | Descending

Type called "ConditionalEncoding":
    test as LogicalOperand
    then_encoding as Encoding
    else_encoding as Optional[Encoding]

Type called "LogicalOperand":
    operand_type as LogicalOperandType
    field as Optional[String]
    value as Optional[Any]
    selection as Optional[String]

Type LogicalOperandType is:
    | FieldEqualTo
    | FieldLessThan
    | FieldGreaterThan
    | FieldRange
    | OneOf
    | Selection

Type called "Faceting":
    facet_type as FacetType
    field as String
    columns as Optional[Integer]
    spacing as Float
    align as Boolean

Type FacetType is:
    | Row
    | Column
    | Wrap

Type called "CoordinateSystem":
    coord_type as CoordinateType
    flip as Boolean
    transpose as Boolean
    clip as Boolean

Type CoordinateType is:
    | Cartesian_
    | Polar_
    | Mercator
    | AlbersUSA
    | Orthographic
    | Stereographic

Type called "PlotTheme":
    background as PlotCore.Color
    grid_color as PlotCore.Color
    text_color as PlotCore.Color
    axis_color as PlotCore.Color
    font_family as String
    font_size as Float
    plot_background as PlotCore.Color
    legend_background as PlotCore.Color
    strip_background as PlotCore.Color

Note: Core declarative plotting API
Process called "create_plot_spec" that takes data as DataSource returns PlotSpec:
    Return PlotSpec with:
    data as data
    encodings as dictionary containing
    marks as list containing
    transforms as list containing
    scales as dictionary containing
    facet as None
    coordinates as create_default_coordinate_system()
    theme as create_default_theme()
    title as None
    width as None
    height as None

Process called "encode" that takes spec as PlotSpec and channel as EncodingChannel and field as String and data_type as Optional[DataType] returns PlotSpec:
    Let inferred_type be data_type or infer_data_type with data as spec.data and field as field Let encoding be Encoding with:
    channel as channel
    field as field
    data_type as inferred_type
    scale as None
    bin as None
    aggregate as None
    sort as None
    condition as None Set spec.encodings[String.from with value as channel] to encoding
    Return spec

Process called "mark" that takes spec as PlotSpec and mark_type as MarkType and properties as Optional[MarkProperties] returns PlotSpec:
    Let mark_props be properties or create_default_mark_properties() Let new_mark be Mark with:
    mark_type as mark_type
    properties as mark_props
    encodings as Collections.Dict.copy with dict as spec.encodings
    transforms as Collections.List.copy with lst as spec.transforms
    interactive as false Add new_mark to spec.marks
    Return spec

Process called "transform" that takes spec as PlotSpec and transform_type as TransformType and parameters as Dictionary[String, Any] returns PlotSpec:
    Let new_transform be Transform with:
    transform_type as transform_type
    parameters as parameters Add new_transform to spec.transforms
    Return spec

Process called "scale" that takes spec as PlotSpec and channel as EncodingChannel and scale_type as ScaleType and domain as Optional[ScaleDomain] and range as Optional[ScaleRange] returns PlotSpec:
    Let new_scale be Scale with:
    scale_type as scale_type
    domain as domain
    range as range
    interpolate as None
    padding as 0.1
    zero as true
    nice as true
    clamp as false Set spec.scales[String.from with value as channel] to new_scale
    Return spec

Process called "facet_wrap" that takes spec as PlotSpec and field as String and columns as Optional[Integer] returns PlotSpec:
    Let facet_spec be Faceting with:
    facet_type as Wrap
    field as field
    columns as columns or 3
    spacing as 0.1
    align as true Set spec.facet to facet_spec
    Return spec

Process called "facet_grid" that takes spec as PlotSpec and row_field as Optional[String] and col_field as Optional[String] returns PlotSpec:
    Note: Create grid faceting based on row and/or column fields
    If row_field is not None:
    Let row_facet be Faceting with:
    facet_type as Row
    field as row_field
    columns as None
    spacing as 0.1
    align as true
    Set spec.facet to row_facet If col_field is not None:
    Let col_facet be Faceting with:
    facet_type as Column
    field as col_field
    columns as None
    spacing as 0.1
    align as true
    Set spec.facet to col_facet Return spec

Process called "theme" that takes spec as PlotSpec and theme as PlotTheme returns PlotSpec:
    Set spec.theme to theme
    Return spec

Note: Statistical transformations
Process called "stat_smooth" that takes spec as PlotSpec and method as Optional[String] and se as Optional[Boolean] returns PlotSpec:
    Let smooth_method be method or "loess"
    Let show_se be se or true Let smooth_transform be Transform with:
    transform_type as Loess
    parameters as dictionary containing "method" and smooth_method and "se" and show_se Add smooth_transform to spec.transforms
    Return spec

Process called "stat_bin" that takes spec as PlotSpec and bins as Optional[Integer] and binwidth as Optional[Float] returns PlotSpec:
    Let bin_config be Binning with:
    max_bins as bins
    extent as None
    base as None
    step as binwidth
    steps as None
    minstep as None
    divide as None
    nice as true Let bin_transform be Transform with:
    transform_type as Bin_
    parameters as dictionary containing "binning" and bin_config Add bin_transform to spec.transforms
    Return spec

Process called "stat_summary" that takes spec as PlotSpec and fun as Optional[String] and geom as Optional[MarkType] returns PlotSpec:
    Let summary_function be fun or "mean"
    Let summary_geom be geom or Point Let summary_transform be Transform with:
    transform_type as Aggregate_
    parameters as dictionary containing "function" and summary_function and "geom" and summary_geom Add summary_transform to spec.transforms
    Return spec

Process called "stat_density" that takes spec as PlotSpec and adjust as Optional[Float] and kernel as Optional[String] returns PlotSpec:
    Let bandwidth_adjust be adjust or 1.0
    Let kernel_type be kernel or "gaussian"
    Let density_transform be Transform with:
    transform_type as Density
    parameters as dictionary containing "adjust" and bandwidth_adjust and "kernel" and kernel_type Add density_transform to spec.transforms
    Return spec

Note: High-level plotting functions
Process called "plot_scatter" that takes data as DataSource and x as String and y as String returns PlotSpec:
    Let spec be create_plot_spec with data as data
    Set spec to encode with spec as spec and channel as X and field as x and data_type as Quantitative
    Set spec to encode with spec as spec and channel as Y and field as y and data_type as Quantitative
    Set spec to mark with spec as spec and mark_type as Point and properties as None
    Return spec

Process called "plot_line" that takes data as DataSource and x as String and y as String returns PlotSpec:
    Let spec be create_plot_spec with data as data
    Set spec to encode with spec as spec and channel as X and field as x and data_type as Quantitative
    Set spec to encode with spec as spec and channel as Y and field as y and data_type as Quantitative
    Set spec to mark with spec as spec and mark_type as Line_ and properties as None
    Return spec

Process called "plot_bar" that takes data as DataSource and x as String and y as String returns PlotSpec:
    Let spec be create_plot_spec with data as data
    Set spec to encode with spec as spec and channel as X and field as x and data_type as Ordinal
    Set spec to encode with spec as spec and channel as Y and field as y and data_type as Quantitative
    Set spec to mark with spec as spec and mark_type as Bar_ and properties as None
    Return spec

Process called "plot_histogram" that takes data as DataSource and x as String and bins as Optional[Integer] returns PlotSpec:
    Let spec be create_plot_spec with data as data
    Set spec to encode with spec as spec and channel as X and field as x and data_type as Quantitative
    Set spec to encode with spec as spec and channel as Y and field as "count" and data_type as Quantitative
    Set spec to stat_bin with spec as spec and bins as bins and binwidth as None
    Set spec to mark with spec as spec and mark_type as Bar_ and properties as None
    Return spec

Process called "plot_boxplot" that takes data as DataSource and x as String and y as String returns PlotSpec:
    Let spec be create_plot_spec with data as data
    Set spec to encode with spec as spec and channel as X and field as x and data_type as Ordinal
    Set spec to encode with spec as spec and channel as Y and field as y and data_type as Quantitative
    Set spec to mark with spec as spec and mark_type as ErrorBar and properties as None
    Return spec

Process called "plot_violin" that takes data as DataSource and x as String and y as String returns PlotSpec:
    Let spec be create_plot_spec with data as data
    Set spec to encode with spec as spec and channel as X and field as x and data_type as Ordinal
    Set spec to encode with spec as spec and channel as Y and field as y and data_type as Quantitative
    Set spec to stat_density with spec as spec and adjust as None and kernel as None
    Set spec to mark with spec as spec and mark_type as Area and properties as None
    Return spec

Process called "plot_heatmap" that takes data as DataSource and x as String and y as String and fill as String returns PlotSpec:
    Let spec be create_plot_spec with data as data
    Set spec to encode with spec as spec and channel as X and field as x and data_type as Ordinal
    Set spec to encode with spec as spec and channel as Y and field as y and data_type as Ordinal
    Set spec to encode with spec as spec and channel as Color and field as fill and data_type as Quantitative
    Set spec to mark with spec as spec and mark_type as Rect and properties as None
    Return spec

Note: Advanced aesthetic mappings
Process called "map_color" that takes spec as PlotSpec and field as String and palette as Optional[String] returns PlotSpec:
    Let color_palette be palette or "viridis"
    Let color_range be ScaleRange with:
    range_type as Scheme
    values as list containing color_palette Let color_scale be Scale with:
    scale_type as Linear__
    domain as None
    range as color_range
    interpolate as None
    padding as 0.0
    zero as false
    nice as true
    clamp as false Set spec to encode with spec as spec and channel as Color and field as field and data_type as Quantitative
    Set spec to scale with spec as spec and channel as Color and scale_type as Linear__ and domain as None and range as color_range Return spec

Process called "map_size" that takes spec as PlotSpec and field as String and range as Optional[List[Float]] returns PlotSpec:
    Let size_range be range or list containing 1.0, 10.0 Let size_range_spec be ScaleRange with:
    range_type as Literal_
    values as size_range Set spec to encode with spec as spec and channel as Size and field as field and data_type as Quantitative
    Set spec to scale with spec as spec and channel as Size and scale_type as Linear__ and domain as None and range as size_range_spec Return spec

Process called "map_shape" that takes spec as PlotSpec and field as String returns PlotSpec:
    Set spec to encode with spec as spec and channel as Shape and field as field and data_type as Ordinal
    Return spec

Process called "map_alpha" that takes spec as PlotSpec and field as String and range as Optional[List[Float]] returns PlotSpec:
    Let alpha_range be range or list containing 0.1, 1.0 Let alpha_range_spec be ScaleRange with:
    range_type as Literal_
    values as alpha_range Set spec to encode with spec as spec and channel as Opacity and field as field and data_type as Quantitative
    Set spec to scale with spec as spec and channel as Opacity and scale_type as Linear__ and domain as None and range as alpha_range_spec Return spec

Note: Data manipulation and filtering
Process called "filter_data" that takes spec as PlotSpec and field as String and operator as FilterOperator and value as Any returns PlotSpec:
    Let filter_transform be Transform with:
    transform_type as Filter_
    parameters as dictionary containing "field" and field and "operator" and operator and "value" and value Add filter_transform to spec.transforms
    Return spec

Process called "mutate" that takes spec as PlotSpec and field_name as String and expression as String returns PlotSpec:
    Let calculate_transform be Transform with:
    transform_type as Calculate
    parameters as dictionary containing "field" and field_name and "expression" and expression Add calculate_transform to spec.transforms
    Return spec

Process called "summarize" that takes spec as PlotSpec and group_by as List[String] and aggregations as List[Aggregation] returns PlotSpec:
    Let aggregate_transform be Transform with:
    transform_type as Aggregate_
    parameters as dictionary containing "groupby" and group_by and "aggregate" and aggregations Add aggregate_transform to spec.transforms
    Return spec

Process called "arrange" that takes spec as PlotSpec and fields as List[String] and orders as List[SortOrder] returns PlotSpec:
    Note: Create sorting transforms for each field
    For i from 0 to Collections.List.length with lst as fields - 1:
    Let field be fields at index i
    Let order be if i is less than Collections.List.length with lst as orders then orders at index i else Ascending Let sort_spec be Sorting with:
    field as field
    order as order
    by_encoding as None Let sort_transform be Transform with:
    transform_type as Window
    parameters as dictionary containing "sort" and sort_spec Add sort_transform to spec.transforms Return spec

Note: Coordinate transformations
Process called "coord_flip" that takes spec as PlotSpec returns PlotSpec:
    Set spec.coordinates.flip to true
    Return spec

Process called "coord_polar" that takes spec as PlotSpec returns PlotSpec:
    Set spec.coordinates.coord_type to Polar_
    Return spec

Process called "coord_cartesian" that takes spec as PlotSpec and xlim as Optional[List[Float]] and ylim as Optional[List[Float]] returns PlotSpec:
    Set spec.coordinates.coord_type to Cartesian_ If xlim is not None:
    Let x_domain be ScaleDomain with:
    domain_type as Literal
    values as xlim
    Set spec.scales["X"] to Scale with:
    scale_type as Linear__
    domain as x_domain
    range as None
    interpolate as None
    padding as 0.0
    zero as false
    nice as false
    clamp as true If ylim is not None:
    Let y_domain be ScaleDomain with:
    domain_type as Literal
    values as ylim
    Set spec.scales["Y"] to Scale with:
    scale_type as Linear__
    domain as y_domain
    range as None
    interpolate as None
    padding as 0.0
    zero as false
    nice as false
    clamp as true Return spec

Note: Theming and customization
Process called "theme_minimal" returns PlotTheme:
    Return PlotTheme with:
    background as PlotCore.create_white_color()
    grid_color as PlotCore.create_color with red as 0.9 and green as 0.9 and blue as 0.9 and alpha as 1.0
    text_color as PlotCore.create_color with red as 0.2 and green as 0.2 and blue as 0.2 and alpha as 1.0
    axis_color as PlotCore.create_color with red as 0.8 and green as 0.8 and blue as 0.8 and alpha as 1.0
    font_family as "Arial, sans-serif"
    font_size as 11.0
    plot_background as PlotCore.create_white_color()
    legend_background as PlotCore.create_white_color()
    strip_background as PlotCore.create_color with red as 0.95 and green as 0.95 and blue as 0.95 and alpha as 1.0

Process called "theme_dark" returns PlotTheme:
    Return PlotTheme with:
    background as PlotCore.create_color with red as 0.1 and green as 0.1 and blue as 0.1 and alpha as 1.0
    grid_color as PlotCore.create_color with red as 0.3 and green as 0.3 and blue as 0.3 and alpha as 1.0
    text_color as PlotCore.create_color with red as 0.9 and green as 0.9 and blue as 0.9 and alpha as 1.0
    axis_color as PlotCore.create_color with red as 0.5 and green as 0.5 and blue as 0.5 and alpha as 1.0
    font_family as "Arial, sans-serif"
    font_size as 11.0
    plot_background as PlotCore.create_color with red as 0.15 and green as 0.15 and blue as 0.15 and alpha as 1.0
    legend_background as PlotCore.create_color with red as 0.2 and green as 0.2 and blue as 0.2 and alpha as 1.0
    strip_background as PlotCore.create_color with red as 0.25 and green as 0.25 and blue as 0.25 and alpha as 1.0

Process called "theme_publication" returns PlotTheme:
    Return PlotTheme with:
    background as PlotCore.create_white_color()
    grid_color as PlotCore.create_color with red as 0.95 and green as 0.95 and blue as 0.95 and alpha as 1.0
    text_color as PlotCore.create_black_color()
    axis_color as PlotCore.create_black_color()
    font_family as "Times New Roman, serif"
    font_size as 12.0
    plot_background as PlotCore.create_white_color()
    legend_background as PlotCore.create_white_color()
    strip_background as PlotCore.create_color with red as 0.98 and green as 0.98 and blue as 0.98 and alpha as 1.0

Note: Plot compilation and rendering
Process called "compile_plot" that takes spec as PlotSpec returns PlotCore.Figure:
    Let figure be PlotCore.create_figure with width as spec.width and height as spec.height and dpi as None Note: Apply transforms to data
    Let transformed_data be apply_transforms with data as spec.data and transforms as spec.transforms Note: Create subplot(s) based on faceting
    If spec.facet is not None:
    create_faceted_subplots with figure as figure and spec as spec and data as transformed_data
    Otherwise:
    Let subplot be PlotCore.add_subplot with figure as figure and rows as 1 and cols as 1 and index as 1
    render_marks_to_subplot with subplot as subplot and spec as spec and data as transformed_data Note: Apply theme
    apply_theme_to_figure with figure as figure and theme as spec.theme Return figure

Process called "render_plot" that takes spec as PlotSpec returns PlotCore.Figure:
    Let figure be compile_plot with spec as spec
    PlotCore.render_figure with figure as figure and backend as None
    Return figure

Process called "save_plot" that takes spec as PlotSpec and filename as String and width as Optional[Float] and height as Optional[Float] returns Boolean:
    If width is not None:
    Set spec.width to width
    If height is not None:
    Set spec.height to height Let figure be compile_plot with spec as spec
    Return PlotCore.save_figure with figure as figure and filename as filename and format as None

Note: Utility functions
Process called "create_default_coordinate_system" returns CoordinateSystem:
    Return CoordinateSystem with:
    coord_type as Cartesian_
    flip as false
    transpose as false
    clip as true

Process called "create_default_theme" returns PlotTheme:
    Return theme_minimal()

Process called "create_default_mark_properties" returns MarkProperties:
    Return MarkProperties with:
    filled as true
    stroke_width as 1.0
    stroke_dash as list containing
    opacity as 1.0
    size as 4.0
    angle as 0.0
    align as Left_
    baseline as Alphabetic
    font as "Arial"
    font_size as 11.0
    font_weight as Normal_

Process called "infer_data_type" that takes data as DataSource and field as String returns DataType:
    Note: Infer data type from field values
    If Collections.Dict.contains_key with dict as data.types and key as field:
    Return data.types[field] Note: Simple heuristic - check first few values
    Return Quantitative

Process called "create_data_source" that takes name as String and data as NDArray.NDArray and columns as List[String] returns DataSource:
    Return DataSource with:
    name as name
    data as data
    columns as columns
    types as infer_column_types with data as data and columns as columns
    metadata as dictionary containing

Process called "infer_column_types" that takes data as NDArray.NDArray and columns as List[String] returns Dictionary[String, DataType]:
    Let types be dictionary containing For each column in columns:
    Set types[column] to Quantitative Return types

Note: Transform application
Process called "apply_transforms" that takes data as DataSource and transforms as List[Transform] returns DataSource:
    Let current_data be data For each transform in transforms:
    Set current_data to apply_single_transform with data as current_data and transform as transform Return current_data

Process called "apply_single_transform" that takes data as DataSource and transform as Transform returns DataSource:
    Match transform.transform_type:
    When Filter_:
    Return apply_filter_transform with data as data and params as transform.parameters
    When Aggregate_:
    Return apply_aggregate_transform with data as data and params as transform.parameters
    When Calculate:
    Return apply_calculate_transform with data as data and params as transform.parameters
    When Bin_:
    Return apply_bin_transform with data as data and params as transform.parameters
    When Density:
    Return apply_density_transform with data as data and params as transform.parameters
    Otherwise:
    Return data

Process called "apply_filter_transform" that takes data as DataSource and params as Dictionary[String, Any] returns DataSource:
    Note: Apply filtering based on parameters
    Return create_filtered_data_source with original as data and filter_params as params

Process called "apply_aggregate_transform" that takes data as DataSource and params as Dictionary[String, Any] returns DataSource:
    Note: Apply aggregation based on parameters
    Return create_aggregated_data_source with original as data and agg_params as params

Process called "apply_calculate_transform" that takes data as DataSource and params as Dictionary[String, Any] returns DataSource:
    Note: Add calculated field based on expression
    Return create_calculated_data_source with original as data and calc_params as params

Process called "apply_bin_transform" that takes data as DataSource and params as Dictionary[String, Any] returns DataSource:
    Note: Apply binning transformation
    Return create_binned_data_source with original as data and bin_params as params

Process called "apply_density_transform" that takes data as DataSource and params as Dictionary[String, Any] returns DataSource:
    Note: Calculate kernel density
    Return create_density_data_source with original as data and density_params as params

Note: Faceting and layout
Process called "create_faceted_subplots" that takes figure as PlotCore.Figure and spec as PlotSpec and data as DataSource:
    Let facet_config be spec.facet or create_default_faceting() Match facet_config.facet_type:
    When Wrap:
    create_wrap_facets with figure as figure and spec as spec and data as data and config as facet_config
    When Row:
    create_row_facets with figure as figure and spec as spec and data as data and config as facet_config
    When Column:
    create_column_facets with figure as figure and spec as spec and data as data and config as facet_config

Process called "create_wrap_facets" that takes figure as PlotCore.Figure and spec as PlotSpec and data as DataSource and config as Faceting:
    Note: Create wrapped facet layout
    Let unique_values be get_unique_values with data as data and field as config.field
    Let n_facets be Collections.List.length with lst as unique_values
    Let n_cols be config.columns or 3
    Let n_rows be Integer.from with value as Math.ceil with x as Float.from with value as n_facets divided by Float.from with value as n_cols For i from 0 to n_facets - 1:
    Let subplot be PlotCore.add_subplot with figure as figure and rows as n_rows and cols as n_cols and index as (i 1)
    Let facet_data be filter_data_by_value with data as data and field as config.field and value as unique_values at index i
    render_marks_to_subplot with subplot as subplot and spec as spec and data as facet_data

Process called "render_marks_to_subplot" that takes subplot as PlotCore.Subplot and spec as PlotSpec and data as DataSource:
    For each mark in spec.marks:
    render_single_mark with subplot as subplot and mark as mark and data as data and encodings as spec.encodings and scales as spec.scales

Process called "render_single_mark" that takes subplot as PlotCore.Subplot and mark as Mark and data as DataSource and encodings as Dictionary[String, Encoding] and scales as Dictionary[String, Scale]:
    Note: Extract data for x and y encodings
    Let x_data be extract_encoding_data with data as data and encoding as encodings["X"] and scales as scales
    Let y_data be extract_encoding_data with data as data and encoding as encodings["Y"] and scales as scales Match mark.mark_type:
    When Point:
    PlotCore.scatter_plot with subplot as subplot and x_data as x_data and y_data as y_data and style as convert_mark_to_style with mark as mark
    When Line_:
    PlotCore.plot_line with subplot as subplot and x_data as x_data and y_data as y_data and style as convert_mark_to_style with mark as mark
    When Bar_:
    PlotCore.bar_chart with subplot as subplot and x_data as x_data and heights as y_data and width as None and style as convert_mark_to_style with mark as mark
    When Area:
    render_area_mark with subplot as subplot and x_data as x_data and y_data as y_data and mark as mark
    When Rect:
    render_rect_mark with subplot as subplot and x_data as x_data and y_data as y_data and mark as mark and encodings as encodings
    Otherwise:
    render_generic_mark with subplot as subplot and mark as mark and data as data

Note: Style conversion and rendering helpers
Process called "convert_mark_to_style" that takes mark as Mark returns PlotCore.Style:
    Return PlotCore.Style with:
    color as PlotCore.create_blue_color()
    line_width as mark.properties.stroke_width
    line_style as PlotCore.Solid
    marker as create_marker_from_properties with props as mark.properties
    marker_size as mark.properties.size
    fill_color as if mark.properties.filled then PlotCore.create_blue_color() else None
    edge_color as PlotCore.create_black_color()
    hatch_pattern as None

Process called "create_marker_from_properties" that takes props as MarkProperties returns PlotCore.Marker:
    Return PlotCore.Marker with:
    symbol as PlotCore.Circle
    size as props.size
    edge_width as props.stroke_width
    edge_color as PlotCore.create_black_color()
    fill_color as PlotCore.create_blue_color()

Process called "extract_encoding_data" that takes data as DataSource and encoding as Encoding and scales as Dictionary[String, Scale] returns NDArray.NDArray:
    Note: Extract and transform data based on encoding specification
    Let field_index be find_field_index with data as data and field as encoding.field
    Return extract_column_data with data as data and column_index as field_index

Process called "find_field_index" that takes data as DataSource and field as String returns Integer:
    For i from 0 to Collections.List.length with lst as data.columns - 1:
    If data.columns at index i is equal to field:
    Return i
    Return 0

Process called "extract_column_data" that takes data as DataSource and column_index as Integer returns NDArray.NDArray:
    Let n_rows be data.data.shape at index 0
    Let column_data be NDArray.zeros with shape as list containing n_rows For i from 0 to n_rows - 1:
    Set column_data.data at index i to data.data.data at index (i multiplied by data.data.shape at index 1 column_index) Return column_data

Note: Simplified implementations for complex functions
Process called "apply_theme_to_figure" that takes figure as PlotCore.Figure and theme as PlotTheme:
    Set figure.background_color to theme.background
    Note: Apply theme colors and fonts to figure elements
    Return

Process called "get_unique_values" that takes data as DataSource and field as String returns List[Any]:
    Note: Get unique values from field
    Return list containing "A", "B", "C"

Process called "filter_data_by_value" that takes data as DataSource and field as String and value as Any returns DataSource:
