Note: Convenience functions for common plot patterns
Process called "quick_plot" that takes data as NDArray.NDArray and columns as List[String] and x as String and y as String and plot_type as MarkType returns PlotCore.Figure:
    Let data_source be create_data_source with name as "data" and data as data and columns as columns Let spec be create_plot_spec with data as data_source
    Set spec to encode with spec as spec and channel as X and field as x and data_type as None
    Set spec to encode with spec as spec and channel as Y and field as y and data_type as None
    Set spec to mark with spec as spec and mark_type as plot_type and properties as None Return compile_plot with spec as spec

Process called "layered_plot" that takes specs as List[PlotSpec] returns PlotCore.Figure:
    Note: Combine multiple plot specifications into layers
    Let base_spec be specs at index 0
    Let figure be compile_plot with spec as base_spec Note: Add additional layers
    For i from 1 to Collections.List.length with lst as specs - 1:
    Let layer_spec be specs at index i
    add_layer_to_figure with figure as figure and spec as layer_spec Return figure

Process called "add_layer_to_figure" that takes figure as PlotCore.Figure and spec as PlotSpec:
    Note: Add plot specification as new layer
    Return